trans-unit.source: Provides data for splitter events.
The following code example demonstrates the use of this type.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo de código siguiente se muestra el uso de este tipo.

trans-unit.source: In the example, an event handler reports on the occurrence of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.SplitContainer.SplitterMoving> event.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo, un controlador de eventos notifica la aparición de la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.SplitContainer.SplitterMoving> eventos.

trans-unit.source: This report helps you to learn when the event occurs and can assist you in debugging.

trans-unit.source: To report on multiple events or on events that occur frequently, consider replacing <xref:System.Windows.Forms.MessageBox.Show%2A> with <xref:System.Console.WriteLine%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> or appending the message to a multiline <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TextBox>.

trans-unit.source: To run the example code, paste it into a project that contains an instance of type <xref:System.Windows.Forms.SplitContainer> named `SplitContainer1`.
trans-unit.target: Para ejecutar el ejemplo de código, péguelo en un proyecto que contiene una instancia del tipo <xref:System.Windows.Forms.SplitContainer> denominado `SplitContainer1`.

trans-unit.source: Then ensure that the event handler is associated with the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.SplitContainer.SplitterMoving> event.
trans-unit.target: A continuación, asegúrese de que el controlador de eventos esté asociado el <xref:System.Windows.Forms.SplitContainer.SplitterMoving> eventos.

trans-unit.source: The X coordinate of the mouse pointer in client coordinates.
The Y coordinate of the mouse pointer in client coordinates.
The X coordinate of the upper left corner of the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.SplitContainer" /> in client coordinates.
The Y coordinate of the upper left corner of the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.SplitContainer" /> in client coordinates.

Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.SplitterCancelEventArgs" /> class with the specified coordinates of the mouse pointer and the upper left corner of the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.SplitContainer" />.
Gets the X coordinate of the mouse pointer in client coordinates.
An integer representing the X coordinate of the mouse pointer in client coordinates.
trans-unit.target: Un entero que representa la coordenada X del puntero del mouse en coordenadas de cliente.
